  "text": "Algebraic Aggregate Functions. We implement algebraic aggregate functions (i.e., ones that use a fixed amount of state) [CITATION_1] in a straightforward fashion. To implement count, e.g., we use a standard counter component and wire its trigger input to the data valid signal of the input stream. Once we reach the end of the current stream, we (a) emit the counter value to the upstream data path and (b) reset the counter to zero to prepare for the next input stream.",
